@startuml Teacher_UploadMaterials_Seq
title EduFlow LMS — Teacher: Upload Materials Sequence

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipant underline
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF

actor       Teacher          as T
participant "EduFlow UI"     as UI
participant "Material Service" as MS
participant "File Storage"   as FS
participant "Database"       as DB
participant "Notification Service" as NS
actor       Student          as S

== Upload New Material ==

T -> UI : Navigate to Course > Materials
UI -> MS : GET /courses/{course_id}/materials
MS -> DB : SELECT materials for course
DB --> MS : materials[]
MS --> UI : Return list
UI --> T  : Display materials panel

T -> UI : Click "Upload" & select file(s)
UI -> FS : POST /upload { file, metadata }
FS -> FS : Validate file type & size
alt File valid
    FS -> FS : Store file, generate URL
    FS --> UI : { file_url, file_id }
    UI -> MS : POST /materials { course_id, file_id,\n title, description, visibility }
    MS -> DB : INSERT material record
    DB --> MS : material_id
    MS --> UI : 201 Created { material_id }
    UI --> T  : "Material uploaded successfully"
    MS -> NS  : Notify enrolled students
    NS -> S   : Push / Email: "New material available"
else File invalid
    FS --> UI : 400 Bad Request (type/size error)
    UI --> T  : Show error message
end

== Update Existing Material ==

T -> UI : Select material > "Edit"
T -> UI : Modify title / description / replace file
UI -> MS : PUT /materials/{material_id} { changes }
MS -> DB : UPDATE material record
DB --> MS : OK
MS --> UI : 200 OK
UI --> T  : "Material updated"

== Delete Material ==

T -> UI  : Select material > "Delete"
UI --> T : Confirmation dialog
T -> UI  : Confirm deletion
UI -> MS : DELETE /materials/{material_id}
MS -> DB : DELETE material record
MS -> FS : DELETE stored file
DB --> MS : OK
MS --> UI : 204 No Content
UI --> T  : "Material removed"

@enduml
